  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Activity
    An activity represents a seance
    Attendance
    An attendance is the marker of a client's attendance to an acitity The pay is calculated from Attendances.
    Client
    Represents a Client for the gym
    ClientReporter
    Used to create the Client Reports.
    DataStore
    Simulation of a Database for our homework In real life, would be an interface to a SQL database.
    Entity
    An Entity is an IRL person (so a Client or a Professional).
    GymClass
    All gym entries seem to have a timestamp and a comment field: this GymClass allows us to generate the timestamp automatically.
    Main
    Main is the interface with the oustide world.
    ManagerReporter
    The Reporter for the Manager report
    ProfessionalReporter
    The Reporter for Pros
    Professionnal
    Represents a Real Life profesionnal
    Prototype
    The Prototype is the meat of the program.
    PrototypeTest
    Tests on the prototype
    QRUtils
    Utilitary class for QR codes.
    Reporter
    Reporter is an abstract Reporter class.
    Stamp
    A Stamp is a wrapper around a sql.Timestamp We need this class to make it compatible with the time formats specified in the requirements: sql.Timestamp does not respect it.
    StringUtils
    StringUtils contains helpful string fonctions
    UUID
    UUID is a representation of a unique ID.
    UUID7
    Helper class for reflection: simply a UUID of fixed size 7
    UUID9
    Helper class for reflection: simply a UUID of fixed size 9
    UuidGymClass
    Helper interface for IDEs: specifies that certain GymClasses contain an UUID and they should implement a getUuid method.
    Week
    A week is like a enum for the days of the week (indicating which day is marked as true and which aren't), but it also contains helpful string methods.
